Interstate 87 begins at an intersection with the [[Bruckner_Expressway|Bruckner Expressway]]（[[Interstate_278|I-278]]）at the [[Triborough_Bridge|Triborough Bridge]]。For the next 8.4 miles, Interstate 87 is known as the Major [[William_Francis_Deegan|William Francis Deegan]] Expressway, which travels through the Bronx. The road, formerly [[New_York_State_Route_1B|New York State Route 1B]]，was proposed in 1936 by the [[Regional_Plan_Association|Regional Plan Association]] to relieve traffic issues. The road was first opened in 1939, as a 1.5 mile long highway, ending at [[Grand_Concourse|Grand Concourse]]。[[Robert_Moses|Robert Moses]] worked on getting the expressway to go farther north, with a proposed ending at the to-be [[New_York_State_Thruway|New York State Thruway]]。By [[1956|1956]]，the Major Deegan was completed, gaining Interstate status soon after. 
[[File:MajBGS.jpg|left]]
The first exit along the Major Deegan northbound is for Willis Avenue and the nearby [[Third_Avenue_Bridge|Third Avenue Bridge]]。There is an exit before this going southbound, for Brook Avenue. At 1.20 miles, Grand Concourse interchanges at Exit 3. East 149th Street is the next exit, which heads into the heart of the Bronx. Exit 5, which is signed for [[East_161st_Street_(Bronx)|East 161st Street]]，actually lets off at [[Jerome_Avenue|Jerome Avenue]]. Exit 6 is only accessible via Exit 5 (going northbound) and is for East 153rd Street. Exit 7 is for the [[Cross_Bronx_Expressway|Cross Bronx Expressway]] and [[Trans-Manhattan_Expressway|Trans-Manhattan Expressway]]，both of which are signed as I-95 and US 1. Exit 8 is for West 179th Street, which becomes Burnside Avenue soon after. Exit 9 parallels the Major Deegan for ending at West Fordham Road. 

[[U.S._Route_9_in_New_York|U.S. Route 9]] now parallels the Major Deegan, which is accessible via Exit 10 for West 230th Street. Interstate 87 then enters [[Van_Cortlandt_Park|Van Cortlandt Park]] and interchanges with Van Cortlandt Park South at Exit 11. Exit 12 is for the [[Henry_Hudson_Parkway|Henry Hudson Parkway]] and [[Saw_Mill_River_Parkway|Saw Mill River Parkway]]，both of which are accessible by the [[Mosholu_Parkway|Mosholu Parkway]]。Exit 13 is for [[East_233rd_Street_(Bronx)|East 233rd Street]] and [[Jerome_Avenue|Jerome Avenue]]。Exit 14 is at the northern end of Van Cortlandt Park, is for McLean Boulevard. The Major Deegan crosses into [[Westchester|Westchester]] and becomes the [[New_York_State_Thruway|New York State Thruway]]，a 496-mile, state-wide highway.-->

=== 紐約州收費公路 ===
從紐約市到奧本尼與[[90號州際公路|90號州際公路]]交會處是[[紐約州收費公路|紐約州收費公路]]的一部分，在1950年代建成，並在1958年被標為87號州際公路。自紐約市布朗克斯之後，紐約州收費公路經由[[塔班奇大橋|塔班奇大橋]]跨越[[哈德遜河|哈德遜河]]連接[[威斯特徹斯特郡|威斯特徹斯特郡]]與[[羅克蘭郡_(紐約州)|羅克蘭郡]]。

=== 亞迪榮戴克北方公路 ===
在[[奧本尼|奧本尼]]以北的I-87路段稱為亞迪榮戴克北方公路（Adirondack Northway，或簡稱Northway），一直向北前往[[美加邊境|美加邊境]]。這段高速公路在興建期間引起了眾多爭論，因為穿越了[[亞迪榮戴克山脈|亞迪榮戴克山脈]]，但還是在1967年為了[[1967年世界博覽會|1967年世界博覽會]]興建，以連接[[紐約市|紐約市]]與[[蒙特婁|蒙特婁]]。同年[[:en:Parade_Magazine|Parade Magazine]]將這路段命名為「美國風景最儷緻的公路」。。
